actions.title: cm0qeynbw00032ysb32wkfkns_addition
actions.description:
Add two integers.

    Args:
        a: The first integer.
        b: The second integer.

    Returns:
        The sum of a and b.
actions.code:
def addition(a: int, b: int) -> int:
    """
    Add two integers.

    Args:
        a: The first integer.
        b: The second integer.

    Returns:
        The sum of a and b.
    """
    return a + b

actions.title: cm0qeynbw00032ysb32wkfkns_division
actions.description:
Divide two integers.

    Args:
        a: The dividend.
        b: The divisor.

    Returns:
        The result of a divided by b.
        
    Raises:
        ValueError: If b is zero.
actions.code:
def division(a: int, b: int) -> float:
    """
    Divide two integers.

    Args:
        a: The dividend.
        b: The divisor.

    Returns:
        The result of a divided by b.
        
    Raises:
        ValueError: If b is zero.
    """
    if b == 0:
        raise ValueError("Cannot divide by zero")
    return a / b

    Args:

        b: The second integer.

    Returns:
        The product of a and b.
    """
    return a * b

actions.title: cm0qeynbw00032ysb32wkfkns_power
actions.description:
Raise base to the power of exponent.

    Args:
        base: The base integer.
        exponent: The exponent to raise the base to.

    Returns:
        The result of base raised to exponent.
actions.code:
def power(base: int, exponent: int) -> int:
    """
    Raise base to the power of exponent.

    Args:
        base: The base integer.
        exponent: The exponent to raise the base to.

    Returns:
        The result of base raised to exponent.
    """
    return base ** exponent

def subtraction(a: int, b: int) -> int:
    """
    Subtract one integer from another.

    Args:
        a: The first integer.
        b: The second integer.

    Returns:
        The difference between a and b.
    """
    return a - b

actions.title: cm0qgv2vj00072ysbeksc68ft_get_user_list
actions.description:
Give the list user of user
    
    Args:
        count: How many user should return default to 10
        
    
    Returns:
        A list of user
actions.code:
def get_user_list(count: int = 10):
    """
    Give the list user of user
    
    Args:
        count: How many user should return default to 10
        
    
    Returns:
        A list of user
    """
    user_list = []
    
    for i in range(count):
        user_list.append({
            "id": i,
            "name": f"abhishek {i}",
            "email": f"abhishek{i}@mail.com"
        })
    
    return user_list
